Package org.billtorcaso.kutils

Interface Summary
Stopwatch The Stopwatch interface records an sequence of named moments, with nanosecond intervals and minimal run-time overhead.
Stopwatch.Moment The Moment interface represents an immutable "moment in time", consisting of a long integer value and a String title.
 

Class Summary
MomentImpl This class represents a "moment", with a long integer value from System.nanoTime() and a String title.
StopwatchFactory This class is the factory for Stopwatch objects.
StopwatchImpl This class implements the Stopwatch interface.
StopwatchInstance This class provides class-static services for a shareable singleton Stopwatch object.
StopwatchNoOpImpl This class implements the Stopwatch interface but does nothing, so as to minimize the overhead of embedded calls on a Stopwatch.
 

Enum Summary
Stopwatch.IntervalReportType This enum represents the various interpretations of when.
Stopwatch.TimeElapsedType This enum represents the various measures of elapsed time.
 

Annotation Types Summary

Immutable The class to which this annotation is applied is immutable.
NotThreadSafe The class to which this annotation is applied is not thread-safe.
ThreadSafe The class to which this annotation is applied is thread-safe.
